jday
------------------------------------------
A simple command to convert calendar dates to julian dates. Quite useful
intiming situations where you need elapsed time between dates.Also useful for
astronomy applications.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.6.4-1
  libjday-devel-2.4-1bl4
  libjday2-2.4-1bl4
  pkg-config-2.5.1-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-15-2
  autoconf-archive-2024.10.16-1
  automake-20250528-1
  binutils-2.45-1
  cygport-0.37.2-1
  gcc-core-13.4.0-1
  libtool-2.5.4-1
  make-4.4.1-2

Canonical website:
  https://sourceforge.net/projects/jday/

Canonical download:
  mirror://sourceforge/jday/jday-2.4.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack jday-2.4-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./jday-2.4-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/jday-2.4-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/jday-2.4-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libjday2-2.4-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libjday-devel-2.4-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(jday)
  /usr/bin/dbd.exe
  /usr/bin/j2d.exe
  /usr/bin/jday.exe
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/jday.README
  /usr/share/doc/jday/AUTHORS
  /usr/share/doc/jday/COPYING
  /usr/share/doc/jday/ChangeLog
  /usr/share/doc/jday/NEWS
  /usr/share/doc/jday/README
  /usr/share/man/man1/jday.1.gz

(libjday2)
  /usr/bin/cygjday-2.dll

(libjday-devel)
  /usr/include/jday.h
  /usr/lib/libjday.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/jday.pc

